<TEXT>
the possibility of a wave of homeless 
headed for its celebritysoaked shores has malibu in a dither over 
the notion honorary mayor martin sheen may have invited a tent city 
encampment 
sheen declared the beach town where sylvester stallone and 
barbra streisand live a nuclearfree homeless sanctuary 
a nationally syndicated radio talk show host responded by 
calling for a march on malibu on saturday for which he says he 
has 15 buses available as far away as texas by tuesday at least 
one bus load of homeless people was organized in santa barbara 
and that was enough to have the beach community fretting 
if god had intended them to live in malibu hed have made 
them television producers mused los angeles times columnist al 
martinez 
the declaration sparking the turmoil read i hereby declare 
malibu a nuclear free zone a sanctuary for aliens and the homeless 
and a protected environment for all life wild and tame 
the attention sheen has attracted to the beach town of 19000 
has put pressure on the chamber of commerce which appointed him 
honorary mayor earlier this month to promote a shop malibu 
campaign 
the community is pretty upset said mary lou blackwood the 
chambers executive vice president who says she has handled 
hundreds of telephone calls 
malibu is a town with no coin laundry no car wash no mortuary 
and no car lot it has trendy restaurants and three supermarkets 
where its not unusual to see sam elliot amy irving whoopi 
goldberg george c scott or dick van dyke 
few heads turn when stallone roars by on his motorcycle malibu 
is a place where eddie van halen and sammy hagar can jam at the 
trancas nightclub without screaming throngs 
homes start at 500000 and go up to 20 million which is the 
price tag on miss streisands compound despite its 
celebrityenclave stereotype most residents are working stiffs 
with an average annual income of 60000 
sheen neighbor johnny carson joked on the tonight show that 
residents were offering to pay for valet parking for the homeless 
and provide free sunblock the honorary mayor responded to 
criticism by declaring malibu a freespeech zone 
carson said the following night mayor sheen just declared 
michael landons hair a national forest but many local 
malibuites arent amused 
the malibu inn and restaurants dump martin sheen marquee 
changed tuesday to johnny for mayor seemed to express 
prevailing opinion we should disassociate ourselves with him 
there is no community that welcomes the homeless said manager 
tony casson 
friends of sheen who has been heavily involved in antinuclear 
weapons protests and the farm workers grape boycott pledged to 
provide food and clothing if homeless people show up 
were not going to ask them to leave we feel those people 
have suffered enough and they are being used said neighbor maria 
olk supporter judith israel said homeless people arent meat 
new yorkbased conservative radio talk show host rush limbaugh 
who has been needling sheen and the hollywood left coast for 
years said his offer of oneway bus tickets to malibu was a fair 
comment on sheens declaration 
i like to illustrate absurdity with the absurd limbaugh 
said tuesday it is my intention to discredit sheen the march is 
purely to embarrass sheen and not malibu 
limbaugh who embraces programs making the homeless selfreliant 
rather than giving them handouts said he telephoned the chamber to 
ask where to take his homeless bus and a spokeswoman said 
theres no place for them here then hung up 
see theres no sanctuary we are going to show them they 
dont want you said limbaugh conceding his reservations about 
bringing homeless to malibu i dont want to be thought of as a 
cheap theatrical stunt guy 
sheen who has been in canada directing gary busey and son 
charlie sheen in the movie count a lonely cadence said in his 
latest missive from vancouver i regret that my concern for the 
poor and the environment was so dishonestly misinterpreted and 
misused to perpetrate a cruel hoax on 4 million americans who are 
already broken beyond any measure of understanding 
