the reactors would produce tritium a radioactive gas used to 
make nuclear warheads 
one reactor is to be built at the departments savannah river 
site near aiken sc and the other would be new at the idaho 
national engineering laboratory near idaho falls the department 
wants them in production by 1998 as replacements for three 
35yearold savannah river reactors which have been shut down for 
repairs 
peach said recent breakdowns at the existing savannah river 
reactors which are the nations only source of tritium make the 
