report in conjunction with the gao report 
the gao report underscores my subcommittees findings that 
longterm care insurance is simply not a good buy and adequate 
consumer protections are not in place at the state or federal 
level said peppers statement as currently designed nursing 
home policies offer seniors a false sense of security 
pepper said private longterm care insurance can help fill gaps 
in a yettobe developed medicarelike federal nursing home 
program but should be banned from sale as primary coverage for 
longterm care 
in the absence of such a ban only those private longterm 
care insurance policies certified as meeting federal minimum 
standards should be allowed to be sold his statement said 
rep pete stark dcalif chairman of the ways and means health 
subcommittee has introduced a bill to establish such minimum 
federal standards the measure patterned on model legislation 
recommended by the national association of insurance commissioners 
also would provide criminal sanctions against fraudulent sales 
practices 
