meeting soviet proposals for cuts in nonnuclear forces require a 
response from the alliance itself not the united states alone 
still bush signaled a shift in tone 
the president felt he appeared too negative before and hes 
trying to appear more positive now said his national security 
adviser brent scowcroft 
