without borders said autopsies on 16 victims identified 
chloropicrine as one of the gases 
on wednesday the organization said its doctors were denied full 
access to soviet autopsy reports but laboratory analysis of the 
substance allegedly used in tbilisi to disperse 10000 protesters 
april 9 revealed chloropicrine 
chrloropicrine is a highly toxic substance used widely during 
world war i in combat dr benoit nemery a belgian toxicoligist 
told reporters in a telephone connection with a news conference at 
the groups paris headquarters 
it is highly probable that it was used but until we have the 
results of a biological analysis performed on an organ of a victim 
