gospel rescue missions long a champion 
in the inner city for the homeless are responding to a whole new 
range of needs that were practically unthinkable even a decade ago 
expansion in the role of these downtown missions was highlighted 
at the recent annual convention of representatives of about 300 
such missions in cities across the country 
it long has been a stereotype that they mostly serve older 
alcoholics and drug abusers however young adults women and 
children are just as likely to seek help these days 
that has put a growing load on rescue missions to meet needs not 
met by state or other agencies 
in the last 10 to 15 years things have changed drastically 
