<TEXT>
opec nations supplied slightly more oil 
to the world market in april than allowed in a production accord 
designed to lift crude prices the organization said wednesday 
it was the first time this year that the organization of 
petroleum exporting countries reported a supply level above the 
ceiling set in an agreement covering output for the first six 
months of 1989 
private analysts have detected a recent pickup in production by 
opec nations 
subroto secretarygeneral of the 13nation oil organization 
urged the producers to try to sustain the present hardwon 
stability in the market 
production restraint by all producers both inside and outside 
opec is still necessary in view of the fragility of the present 
price structure he was quoted as saying in a statement issued by 
the opec news agency 
the statement said 12 of the 13 members poured 1754 million 
barrels a day into the international market last month 
the production agreement for the first half of 1989 sets a 
supply target of 1751 million barrels a day for the 12 members 
opec said total production by the dozen nations amounted to 
1847 million barrels a day in april figures were not available 
for the united arab emirates it said 
the socalled opec overproduction to which the media has been 
calling attention has not been supplied to the market but has gone 
into building stocks in a concerted effort by member countries not 
to destabilize the market the cartel said 
during january to april the 12 countries added nearly 70 
million barrels to their stocks 383 million barrels to stocks 
held abroad and 316 million to those within national boundaries 
it said 
analysts have attributed the recent increase in production 
partly to an effort by opec nations to stake out positions in 
advance of a key meeting next month in vienna at that gathering 
the oil chiefs will agree on a production level for the second half 
of the year and set individual quotas for each country 
kuwait and the united arab emirates analysts say want a bigger 
share of the overall ceiling negotiated by the producers 
the international energy agency in its monthly oil market 
report estimated opec output at 205 million barrels a day in 
april up from 198 million barrels the previous month 
the current accord worked out in late november set a 
production limit of 185 million barrels a day for the entire 
cartel opec measures a nations quota by figuring crude production 
and the amount of oil put into or drawn out of stocks 
the output ceiling well under december levels was set in an 
effort to boost prices to a target of 18 dollars a barrel 
prices soared beyond that benchmark although the rally has 
eased a bit recently west texas intermediate the benchmark 
american crude has been trading in the range of 19 dollars to 20 
dollars a barrel 
the price surge has been attributed not only to opecs 
production cuts but also to accidents in oilproducing areas that 
have reduced the supply in the world market 
