<TEXT>
to critics the vancouver 
stock exchange has been a hucksters paradise duping investors and 
sucking up capital that could be better used elsewhere 
to defenders the exchange fills a valid and serious economic 
function they say its where entrepreneurs turn to raise the 
startup capital they need a marketplace based in the regions 
mining and resource industries now moving into high technology and 
other innovative businesses 
the exchange has had its fair share of scandal and controversy 
since its founding in 1907 and a new round of criticism from such 
high profile business publications as barrons and forbes has 
placed it back in the spotlight 
we do specialize in venture capital and that by nature is 
risky joyce courtney the exchanges spokeswoman said in an 
interview people have long memories and it seems that people 
remember us by the bad company weve kept 
the exchange claims to be the third most active in volume in 
north america after new york and toronto 
the focus on junior companies as the exchange prefers to 
call its startup offerings and the generally inexpensive price 
tags on their stocks push the volume up a typical trade is 2000 
shares worth a total of 2000 
courtney calls the offerings on the exchange the startup the 
emerging the young 
twothirds of the companies on the vancouver exchange still are 
in precious metal mining the other third and the fastest growing 
area is in such venture capital fields as hightech agriculture 
and franchising 
were still really canadas mining exchange but our world is 
changing too courtney said 
its still buyer beware and people dont like to hear that 
she said the venture market is not for everybody 
i think a lot of the misunderstanding is because we have less 
stringent listing requirements she said people misunderstand 
that and we get labeled the wild west and the casino of the 
north 
indeed donald j hudson the exchanges president said 
firsttime visitors almost invariably express surprise that the 
exchange is not a small operation but employs 320 people in several 
floors spread through a downtown skyscraper 
weve taken the position that the world and canada doesnt 
need another bluechip stock exchange he said our view is 
that weve been in the venture business and we should make that our 
prime thrust 
hudson said that doesnt mean emphasis will be taken away from 
the traditional resourceexploration stocks 
but we are certainly going to do whatever we can to encourage 
listings outside the resource fields he said 
on march 1 the exchange overhauled listings rules and policies 
requiring more complete disclosure about the companies issuing 
stocks 
it added special requirements for companies outside of the 
resourceexploration area partly because some of their stocks have 
raised alarmbells about the potential for hype 
among the hardtoassess stocks that have cropped up on the 
exchange for example are those from companies claiming to offer 
cosmetic franchises treasure hunts and a new way to hull rice 
hudson said it cant be denied that incidents have taken 
place with companies listed on the exchange and they tend to be 
spectacular 
the way to stop all that is stop having incidents he said 
as recently as april former stockbroker dale ciochetti was 
sentenced to three years in prison and fined some 300000 canadian 
dollars or 252000 for for fraud in the rise and fall of 
international tillex enterprises ltd 
the new yorkbased insurance company was underwritten at 20 
canadian cents a share in january 1985 and rose to 77 canadian 
dollars a share in 1986 before the exchange suspended trading 
you cant have it both ways hudson said when asked why 
fraud cases continue to surface if the exchange is making a more 
serious effort to regulate itself than it has in the past 
he objected to those who say proper enforcement doesnt exist 
and then say its all bad when a case is found as a result of 
enforcement 
two years from now we wont have the court cases coming along 
with the frequency theyve been coming along hudson said 
securities commissions operate at provincial level in canada 
and british columbias historically has been weak 
hudson said trading on the vancouver exchange has not recovered 
fully since october 1987 hit harder in value than in volume 
i dont think we have bounced back he said trading has 
been how shall i describe this slow 
he ascribed it to worldwide trends and the slide in the price of 
gold which has weakened the price of many mineral and mining 
stocks 
record volume of 48 billion shares worth 56 billion at 
current exchange rates in 1987 declined to 35 billion shares worth 
27 billion last year the exchanges index of all listed issues 
dropped from 115002 at the end of 1987 to 79272 at the end of 
1988 
elsewhere analysts say a loss of confidence in the exchange 
also has played a part 
john woods publisher of the daily newsletter vancouver 
stockwatch forecast 1989 as a stable year and said the overhaul of 
regulations is a big step in the repair job that the exchange had 
to do to stop its slide into oblivion 
woods said no regulations can erase all bad cases on any 
exchange but the new policies should eliminate what he called the 
joke companies that had proliferated in vancouver over the past 
five years 
you have to conclude that the vse has been weakened he 
said it is not in a good position to recover fast 
 
